inputs.script:
#####
## Only for Master/Release WFE we need to get cluster name from BE build version
## Validation and Standalone FE releases get this info through release variables, and FE deployment invoked through BE/MWC pipelines
## For Master/Release it's not possible yet due to forking - 
## we need to change forking script to allow release BE CST pipelines to call specific FE CST pipeline for this to work
#####

. $(System.DefaultWorkingDirectory)\CSTScripts\common\VstsRestApi.ps1
$version = Get-BuildVersion -BuildId $(Release.Artifacts.BackendBuild.BuildId) -PAT $(System.AccessToken)

if ("$(BackendBuildVersion_Override)" -ne "") {
    "OVERRIDING with $(BackendBuildVersion_Override)"
    $version = "$(BackendBuildVersion_Override)"
}

$ver = [System.Version]$version
$beName = 'cst' + $ver.Build.ToString() + $ver.Revision.ToString()

### # using only CST1 for BE
$beName = "$beName-1" ## PENDING master-vs-release FE refactorings
$feName = "f$beName"

#CST1 is overloaded for some reason for FE
$sCST1 = '4d08a985-6214-43be-8061-0413761b5097'
$sCST2 = '60e238c4-b64e-43a4-9c02-0c7d1d2daf58'
$sCST3 = '1035b0ad-62de-4435-ba04-6eff3722597e'
$sCST4 = '1ce89b38-c7b0-4be9-8870-424e209bc242'
$sCST5 = '99691a02-9de1-4acb-8006-2fc46b4a1218'

$cstSubs = @($sCST1,$sCST2, $sCST3, $sCST4, $sCST5) #Remove subscription from this list in case of constant issues in single subscription

$simpleHash = 0; foreach ($b in [byte[]]($beName).ToCharArray()) { $simpleHash += $b }
$cstSubIndex = [int][Math]::Abs($simpleHash % $cstSubs.Count)
$feSubscription = $cstSubs[$cstSubIndex]

. $(System.DefaultWorkingDirectory)\CSTScripts\DV2\DV2-UpdateReleaseVariable.ps1 -VariableName BackendBuildVersion -VariableValue $version
. $(System.DefaultWorkingDirectory)\CSTScripts\DV2\DV2-UpdateReleaseVariable.ps1 -VariableName CST_BE_Name -VariableValue $beName
. $(System.DefaultWorkingDirectory)\CSTScripts\DV2\DV2-UpdateReleaseVariable.ps1 -VariableName CST_FE_Name -VariableValue $feName
. $(System.DefaultWorkingDirectory)\CSTScripts\DV2\DV2-UpdateReleaseVariable.ps1 -VariableName CST_FE_SubId -VariableValue $feSubscription

environments.triggerReason: ReleaseStarted

workflowTasks.name: Update variable with the CloudVault Upload ObjectId

inputs.script:
#Get Release Definition
$releaseVariableName = 'CloudVault_Upload_ObjectId'
$releaseurl = ('{0}{1}/_apis/release/releases/{2}?api-version=5.0' -f $($env:SYSTEM_TEAMFOUNDATIONSERVERURI), $($env:SYSTEM_TEAMPROJECTID), $($env:RELEASE_RELEASEID)  )

Write-Host "URL: $releaseurl"
$releaseData = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $releaseurl -Headers @{Authorization = "Bearer $env:SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN"}
Write-Output ('Release Pipeline variables output: {0}' -f $($releaseData.variables | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10))

#set Variable value
$releaseData.variables.($releaseVariableName).value = "$(CloudVault_Upload_ObjectId)"


#Updating Release Definition
Write-Output ('Updating Release Definition')
$json = @($releaseData) | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 99
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $releaseurl -Method Put -Body $json -ContentType "application/json" -Headers @{Authorization = "Bearer $env:SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN" }
